</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="177" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,680,1175]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1076,1102]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kuschel" authorityYear="1955" box="[322,504,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Heilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="admixtus">
<emphasis box="[322,504,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Heilus admixtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kuschel" authorityYear="1955" box="[630,806,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Heilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculosus">
<emphasis box="[630,806,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">H. tuberculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pattern of scales on the prosternum and is distinguished from the other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuschel" authorityYear="1955" box="[413,486,1112,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Heilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[413,486,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Heilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the shape of the elytra, flat in the middle, and by the wide range of scales covering the apex of the elytra.
</paragraph>
